{"overview":"A brooding ballad in d minor with a strict ternary design, this piece is defined above all by its bold chain of third-related modulations in the middle section—modal mixture to D major, a diatonic slide through B minor, a further rise to F# major, and then a dramatic enharmonic plunge back to d minor for the recapitulation. The harmonic language throughout is richly chromatic, with modal mixture, deceptive cadences, and prolonged mediant regions lending the piece a dark, epic character rooted in the Romantic ballade tradition.","cross_piece_tags":["ballade","ternary","modal_mixture","enharmonic_modulation","chromatic_mediant","arpeggiated_bass","melancholic","dramatic"]}
